    %h2 Supported Libraries and Platforms
    %p
      Generally version numbers listed here are the earliest
      versions of the relevant thing that have been tested.
      Later versions of those things are also hopefully supported,
      but let us know.
    %h3 Libraries not supported
    %ul
      %li
        versions of Prototype.js before version 1.7 are not supported,
        as they do not support the
        %tt JSON.stringify()
        API correctly.  You
        will get an
        %tt alert()
        in the web page you are debugging if you
        attempt to debug it with
        %span.weinre weinre
        and you are using an unsupported
        version of Prototype.js.
    %h3 Platforms supported - debug server
    %p
      Any platform that supports
      = succeed "." do
        %a{:href => "http://nodejs.org/"} node.js
    %h3 Platforms supported - debug client
    %p
      The browser where the debugger user interface runs.
    %ul
      %li
        Google Chrome
      %li
        Apple Safari
      %li
        Other recent-ish WebKit-based browsers
    %h3 Platforms supported - debug target
    %p
      The browser with the page you are debugging.
    %ul
      %li
        Android Browser application
      %li
        iOS Mobile Safari application
      %li
        PhoneGap/Cordova
      %li
        other
    %h3 Platforms not supported - debug target
    %ul
      %li
        iOS 3.1.3 or earlier
      %li
        webOS 1.45 or earlier
